title.narrative: POLICIES AND STANDARDS FOR NUTRITION SERVICES

description.narrative: Output 2.2 Government is able to produce multi-sectoral policies and standards to guide and monitor nutrition services to the most disadvantaged women and children., which contributes to Nutrition In Early Childhood, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, disadvantaged children have equitable access to health and education services to survive, learn, develop and contribute to resilient, inclusive and sustainable communities

description.narrative: National Integrated Micronutrient and Anthropometric survey was conducted in 2021 to strengthen the National Nutrition Information System, after two years of continuous advocacy, partnership-building and resource mobilization by UNICEF. This nationally representative survey covered 3141 households across the country. The results will inform improvements in the national nutrition plan and promote adequate diets for children. UNICEF played an active role in monitoring legislative reform to safeguard investments in the Law on Breastfeeding and Marketing of Breastmilk substitutes and importing unfortified flour during emergencies. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:24/01/2022
